# Louisepizdon - Project Overview 🥀

## Project Information
- **Full Name**: Louisepizdon  
- **Short Name**: louisepizdon  
- **Description**: AI-powered Telegram bot that evaluates photos and provides funny, detailed pricing breakdowns of items/clothing in the image with witty commentary.  

## Technical Specifications
- **.NET Version**: 9.0+  
- **Main Project**: Louisepizdon.csproj  
- **Architecture**: Console application with modular design  

## Technology Stack
- **Language**: C# 13 (.NET 9.0)  
- **Telegram API**: Telegram.Bot (latest stable)  
- **AI Framework**: Microsoft.Agents.AI (preview)  
- **Caching**: StackExchange.Redis  
- **Cache**: Redis  
- **Containerization**: Docker, docker-compose  

## AI Integration
- **Microsoft.Agents.AI** – AI Agent Framework for LLM integration  
- **Vision Models** – Multi-modal image analysis  
- **OpenAI/OpenRouter** – GPT models with vision capabilities  

## Core Modules (Planned)
- **AI**: Vision analysis and witty response generation  
- **Telegram**: Bot API logic and message handling  
- **Caching**: Redis integration for session/rate limiting  
- **Configuration**: Environment-based configuration  
- **Logging**: Structured logging with Microsoft.Extensions.Logging  

## Key Entry Points
- **Main File**: [Program.cs](mdc:Louisepizdon/Program.cs)  

## Architectural Principles
- **Pattern**: Feature-oriented modular architecture  
- **DI**: Built-in .NET Dependency Injection  
- **Logging**: Structured logging with Microsoft.Extensions.Logging  
- **Configuration**: IOptions pattern with environment variables  
- **Error Handling**: Graceful error handling with logging  

## Bot Functionality
1. User sends a photo to the bot
2. Bot analyzes the image using AI vision
3. Bot generates a funny, itemized price breakdown with witty commentary
4. Response is sent back to the user in Telegram

